	"class": "vulnerability",
	"metadata": {
		"title": "gorilla/schema: Potential memory exhaustion attack due to sparse slice deserialization (important)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2024-37298",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-37298",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: The MITRE CVE dictionary describes this issue as: gorilla/schema converts structs to and from form values. Prior to version 1.4.1 Running `schema.Decoder.Decode()` on a struct that has a field of type `[]struct{...}` opens it up to malicious attacks regarding memory allocations, taking advantage of the sparse slice functionality. Any use of `schema.Decoder.Decode()` on a struct with arrays of other structs could be vulnerable to this memory exhaustion vulnerability. Version 1.4.1 contains a patch for the issue.",
